HEADWORD: Lipic
<hw>Lip"ic</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧p"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>li`pos</grk> fat.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Pertaining to, or
derived from, fat. The word was formerly used specifically to designate
a supposed acid obtained by the oxidation of oleic acid, tallow, wax,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>lipid</ent>⟦br⟧
